ENTRY            F0615   20251216   20260305   20260305       F105
SUBENT        F0615001   20251216   20260305   20260305       F105
BIB                 12         30
TITLE      A study of 31,32,33P by the use of (alpha,p) reactions
           on silicon isotopes
AUTHOR     (N.J.Davis,J.M.Nelson)
INSTITUTE  (2UK BIR)
REFERENCE  (J,JP/G,13,375,1987)
FACILITY   (CYCLO,2UK BIR) Radial Ridge cyclotron.
INC-SOURCE A 25 MeV beam of alpha particles.
SAMPLE     The self-supporting targets were manufactured by
           resistive evaporation of SiO2 to a thickness of
           approximately 100 ug/cm2. Natural silicon dioxide was
           used for the reactions on 28Si and silicon dioxide
           enriched with 29Si or 30Si was used for the reaction
           on those isotopes. The target thicknesses from the
           silicon component were calculated from elastic
           scattering data at 12.5 degr.
DETECTOR   (TELES,SOLST) Pairs of solid state detectors formed
           deltaE-E telescopes, four of which were placed
           5 degr. apart on each of two arms in the scattering
           chamber.
           (SIBAR,SILI) These detectors were used for particle
           identification in conjunction with an analogue
           multiplier.
METHOD     (EDE)
ANALYSIS   The zero-range DWBA calculations were performed.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) No information about source of uncertainty
           (ERR-1) Uncertainty in target thickness
HISTORY    (20031124C)
           (20251216A) SD: Small corrections in all Subents.
           DATA-ERR1 -> DATA-ERR. Subents 002 and 004; 003 and 005
           were merged.
ENDBIB              30
COMMON               3          3
EN         EN-ERR     ERR-1
MEV        KEV        PER-CENT
 25.        150.            5.
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           37
SUBENT        F0615002   20251216   20260305   20260305       F105
BIB                  3          4
REACTION   (14-SI-29(A,P)15-P-32,PAR,DA)
